{"title_page": "Christiaan Rebergen", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific_prefix     = [[Drs.]]\n| name                 = Christiaan Rebergen\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| office               = Treasurer-General\n| term_start           = June 1, 2018\n| predecessor          = [[Hans Vijlbrief]]\n| party                = \n| birth_name           = A.C.C. Rebergen\n| birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1970|5|29}}\n| birth_place          = \n| residence            = \n| children             = 4\n| spouse               = \n| alma_mater           = [[Vrije Universiteit]]\n}}\n'''A.C.C. Rebergen''' (born May 29, 1970) is a Dutch civil servant, who has been serving as the Treasurer-General at the [[Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)|Ministry of Finance]] since 2018.\n\n== Education and career ==\nHe studied general economics at the [[Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam]] after receiving his [[Voorbereidend wetenschappelijk onderwijs|VWO]] diploma at the Christelijk Streeklyceum in [[Ede, Netherlands|Ede]] in 1988. Rebergen graduated seven years later and started working at the Ministry of Finance.<ref name=\"overheid\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/documenten/publicaties/2019/05/24/cv-christiaan-rebergen-thesaurier-generaal |format = PDF |date = 24 May 2019 |access-date = 22 March 2020 |language = Dutch |title = CV Christiaan Rebergen, thesaurier-generaal |website = Rijksoverheid }}</ref>\n\nHe continued serving there with a hiatus at the [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|House of Representatives]] until 2002, when he took a job at the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Netherlands)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]].<ref name=\"overheid\"/> He served as the interim director of Sustainable Economic Development at the ministry between 2006 and March 2012.<ref name=\"overheid\"/><ref>{{Cite press release |url = https://www.algemenebestuursdienst.nl/actueel/nieuws/2012/04/25/christiaan-rebergen-plaatsvervangend-dg-internationale-samenwerking |access-date = 22 March 2020 |language = Dutch |title = Christiaan Rebergen plaatsvervangend DG Internationale Samenwerking |date = 25 April 2012 |website = Algemene Bestuursdienst }}</ref> Additionally, he served as the Ambassador for the [[Millennium Development Goals]] during the last two of those years.<ref name=\"overheid\"/> Rebergen was subsequently promoted to interim Director-General International Cooperation and became the permanent director-general at the end of 2014.<ref>{{Cite press release |url = https://www.algemenebestuursdienst.nl/actueel/nieuws/2014/08/15/christiaan-rebergen-directeur-generaal-internationale-samenwerking-bij-buitenlandse-zaken |access-date = 22 March 2020 |language = Dutch |website = Algemene Bestuursdienst |date = 15 August 2014 |title = Christiaan Rebergen directeur-generaal Internationale Samenwerking bij Buitenlandse Zaken }}</ref>\n\nRebergen returned to the Finance Ministry in June 2018 to serve as Treasurer-General, succeeding [[Hans Vijlbrief]], who had vacated the position to become president of the [[Eurogroup Working Group]].<ref>{{Cite press release |url = https://www.algemenebestuursdienst.nl/actueel/nieuws/2018/04/26/christiaan-rebergen-thesaurier-generaal-bij-financien |website = Algemene Bestuursdienst |access-date = 22 March 2020 |language = Dutch |title = Christiaan Rebergen thesaurier-generaal bij Financi\u00ebn |date = 26 April 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url = https://fd.nl/economie-politiek/1252122/financien-krijgt-rebergen-als-nieuwe-schatkistbewaarder |title = Financi\u00ebn krijgt Christiaan Rebergen als schatkistbewaarder |date = 26 April 2018 |language = Dutch |access-date = 22 March 2020 |website = Het Financieele Dagblad }}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nRebergen is married and has four children.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.esm.europa.eu/board-of-directors/esm/christiaan-rebergen |title = Christiaan Rebergen |website = [[European Stability Mechanism]] |access-date = 24 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-civ}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Hans Vijlbrief]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Treasurer-General|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rebergen, Christiaan}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch civil servants]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch civil servants]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam alumni]]\n[[Category:Treasurers General]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-bio-stub}}\n{{gov-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific_prefix     = [[Drs.]]\n| name                 = Christiaan Rebergen\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| office               = Treasurer General\n| term_start           = June 1, 2018\n| predecessor          = [[Hans Vijlbrief]]\n| party                = \n| birth_name           = A.C.C. Rebergen\n| birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1970|5|29}}\n| birth_place          = \n| residence            = \n| children             = 4\n| spouse               = \n| alma_mater           = [[Vrije Universiteit]]\n}}\n'''A.C.C. Rebergen''' (born May 29, 1970) is a Dutch civil servant, who has been serving as the Treasurer General at the [[Ministry of Finance (Netherlands)|Ministry of Finance]] since 2018.\n\n== Education and career ==\nHe studied general economics at the [[Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam]] after receiving his [[Voorbereidend wetenschappelijk onderwijs|VWO]] diploma at the Christelijk Streeklyceum in [[Ede, Netherlands|Ede]] in 1988. Rebergen graduated seven years later and started working at the Ministry of Finance.<ref name=\"overheid\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/documenten/publicaties/2019/05/24/cv-christiaan-rebergen-thesaurier-generaal |format = PDF |date = 24 May 2019 |access-date = 22 March 2020 |language = Dutch |title = CV Christiaan Rebergen, thesaurier-generaal |website = Rijksoverheid }}</ref>\n\nHe continued serving there with a hiatus at the [[Ho